  "texts": [
    "For merging methods, we notice clear trends that hold regardless of the model.",
    "Task Arithmetic steadily improves as more experts are combined, becoming reliably superior to the base model once a moderate number of experts are merged.",
    "This clearly demonstrates the existence of constructive interference in LLMs: merging several independent fine-tuned checkpoints can produce a model that surpasses both the base LLM and any individual expert.",
    "At the same time, the improvement achieved through merging is modest, generally less than 1% averaged over all tasks.",
    "At most, we can achieve 13.07% improvement for prost task in Llama 3B when all twelve checkpoints are merged with Iso-C."
  ],
